@startuml
title Viaverse Monetization / Billing / Ads — Component Diagram

component "KMP / Business UI\nplans\nbilling\nads dashboard" as Client
component "Admin UI\nplans/fees/coupons\ncampaign config" as Admin
component "API Gateway / BFF\nMonetization API" as BFF
component "MonetizationController\nSubscriptionController\nAdCampaignController" as Controller
component "Monetization Use Cases\nStartSubscription\nCalculateCommission\nCreateSponsoredPlacement\nApplyPromotion" as UseCases
component "Monetization Policies\nplan gates\ncommission rules\nad safety/relevance\nrefund adjustment" as Policies
component "Ports\nBillingRepo\nPaymentPort\nLedgerPort\nSearchAdsPort\nConfigPort\nOutboxPort" as Ports
component "payment-service\nIyzico/Stripe/Masterpass\ncharge/refund/payout" as Payment
database "ledger/accounting\nfee records\ninvoices\nrevenue reports" as Ledger
component "search/ads-service\nsponsored placement\nrelevance gates" as SearchAds
database "PostgreSQL\nplan\nsubscription\ncommission_rule\nad_campaign" as DB
queue "Kafka / Outbox\nSubscriptionStarted\nCommissionCharged\nAdBudgetSpent" as Kafka
component "analytics/reporting\nMRR\nGMV\ntake rate\nLTV/CAC" as Analytics

Client --> BFF : HTTPS
Admin --> BFF : HTTPS admin
BFF --> Controller : REST
Controller --> UseCases : command/query
UseCases --> Policies : validate
Policies --> Ports : ports
Ports --> Payment : money ops
Ports --> Ledger : financial records
Ports --> SearchAds : ads placement
Ports --> DB : config/state
UseCases --> Kafka : events
Ledger --> Analytics : reports

note bottom
Payments, billing rules, ledger, and ads ranking stay separated.
Monetization orchestrates rules but payment-service owns provider integrations and money movement.
end note
@enduml
